5008.0,"debt_to_equity":11.324,"enterprise_value":7688540160.0,"enterprise_to_ebitda":13.381,"enterprise_to_revenue":1.322,"earnings_growth":-0.22,"shares_outstanding":55020000.0,"float_shares":5989069.0,"held_pct_insiders":0.89098,"held_pct_institutions":0.0,"beta":-0.512,"fifty_two_week_high":272.0,"fifty_two_week_low":138.01,"fifty_day_average":165.0874,"two_hundred_day_avg":204.7227,"recommendation":"none","all_time_high":359.95,"all_time_low":145.0,"long_business_summary":"Amines & Plasticizers Limited manufactures and sells specialty chemicals in India. The company offers alkyl alkanol amines, including methyl monoethanolamine, methyl diethanolamine, di-methyl ethanolamine, di-ethyl ethanolamine, ethyl monoethanolamine, ethyl diethanolamine, mono-n-propyl monoethanolamine, mono-n-propyl diethanolamine, mono-n-butyl ethanolamine, mono-n-butyl diethanolamine, di-butyl ethanolamine, poly ethanolamine, tertiary butyl monoethanolamine, and tertiary butyl diethanolamine. It also offers alkanolamines, such as triisopropanolamine, monoethanolamine, diethanolamine, triethanolamine-tech, triethanolamine-pure, and diethanolamine LFG products, as well as morpholine and substituted morpholines comprising morpholine, N-methyl morpholine, N-methyl morpholine oxide, N-ethyl morpholine, N-formyl morpholine, hydroxy ethyl morpholine, N-acetyl morpholine, and N-butyl morpholine. In addition, the company provides specialty ethylene oxide/propylene oxide products that include 2-phenoxy ethanol, 1-piperidine ethanol, diethanol isopropanolamine, N-2 hydroxy ethyl pyrrolidine, and N-benzyl ethanolamine, as well as ethylene oxide/propylene oxide derivatives, such as polypropylene glycol, polyethylene glycol, APOL, amine polyols, glycerol polyol, polyethylene glycol adipates, sorbitol mixture ethoxylates, and alcohol ethoxylates. Further, it offers gas treating products and technologies, such as generic amines, MDEA based specialty amines, and specialty additives, as well as antifoaming agents for gas treating applications. The company serves the pharmaceutical; textile; paints, coatings, printing inks, polyurethanes, metal working fluids, and corrosion inhibitors; agro chemicals; rubber industries and mold releasing agents; photographic chemicals; cement; cosmetic; oil field; acid gas treating; and molecular sieves industries. It also exports its products. Amines & Plasticizers Limited was founded in 1970 and is headquartered in Mumbai, India."}}